# Environment Variables for Deployment
# Copy these to your Vercel dashboard or .env.local file

# Supabase Configuration (Required)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Supabase Service Key (for migration script only - DO NOT use in Vercel)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=your_service_key_here

# OpenAI Configuration (Optional - for AI recommendations)
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# App Configuration (Optional)
VITE_APP_NAME=French Baby Names Explorer
VITE_APP_VERSION=2.0.0

# Instructions for Vercel Deployment:
# 1. Create a new Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Run the schema SQL from database/french-names-schema.sql
# 3. Get your URL and anon key from Supabase project settings
# 4. Add VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY to Vercel environment variables
# 5. Deploy your app to Vercel
# 6. Run the migration script locally to populate the database

# Instructions for Local Development:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in your actual Supabase credentials
# 3. The SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY is only used for data migration
# 4. Never commit the .env.local file to git 